-UNDP has developed a series of short concept notes as immediate response to transition & conflict in April 2014 but long-term umbrella programmes missing;  
-UNDP has a mixed track-record on influencing policy processes in spite of convincing results on the ground;
-No South-South exchanges facilitated since Maidan happened;
-Initial assessments have been conducted of IDP and recovery needs, but have focused primarily on basic needs and infrastructure; assessments have not yet covered reconciliation, human rights, and gender;
-National recovery coordination mechanism has been established, but comprehensive recovery policy not yet established;
-Risks of inter-community tensions in the four oblasts bordering Luhansk, Donesk, and Crimea have not yet been assessed, and systematic local capacities for dialogue and confidence-building not yet established;
-Quick win initiatives have only been launched in Slaviansk, but not comprehensively, and not in all areas restored to government control;
-Issues of transitional justice, human rights, and rule of law in the conflict-affected areas have not yet been subjected to a national debate, and a comprehensive national policy not yet developed.

